I found another area worth checking: the plain `withdraw` path for Bitcoin compresses the refund recipient to exactly 20 bytes before storing it in the revert message. If the protocol ever uses longer non-EVM address encodings there, refunds get misclassified as EVM addresses on revert. I’m checking whether the receiver format is fixed to 20 bytes or not before deciding if that survives.
